benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid Deletion: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03 demonstrate successful removal of one, multiple, and all tags with appropriate status 204 and empty body.
Header Requirements: TC01, TC04, TC09, TC12, TC15 ensure X-Killbill-CreatedBy and additional headers (Reason/Comment) are handled and authorized where applicable.
Error Handling: TC06, TC07, TC08, TC14, TC18 cover invalid accountId, invalid tagDef, malformed tagDef, and regression cases with mixed valid/invalid tagDefs, returning appropriate 4xx errors.
Non-Existent Entity: TC06 and TC07 cover non-existent and invalid accountId formats; TC09 covers missing header error.

Boundary/Edge Cases: TC10 checks business rule (default payment method), TC11 handles extra query params, TC13 tests large numbers of tagDefs, TC15 unauthorized access, TC17 concurrency load, TC19 backward compatibility with omitted optional headers, TC20 empty tagDef array.
Recovery/Resilience: TC12 covers service unavailability, TC16 recovery from transient network failure, TC17 concurrency, TC18 regression for mixed validity of tagDefs.
gaps: Pagination and Large Datasets: No explicit tests for paginating results or handling pagination in DELETE operations (not strictly required for deletions, but guideline mentions pagination generally).
Rate Limiting: No tests verify rate limiting or throttling behavior under high request load.
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching-related headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses.
Soft Deletes/Audit Trails: No explicit test ensuring soft-delete semantics or audit/logging of deletions beyond response semantics.
recommendations: Add a test to simulate and validate behavior under high request rate to exercise rate limiting/throttling.
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses if applicable to the API design.
If applicable to requirements, add a test for soft-delete semantics and/or audit trail visibility on deletions.

Consider an explicit test for edge case of DELETE with very large lists of tagDefs focusing on performance and server-side validation, even if TC13 covers many tags; ensure resource usage remains within SLA.
